### Get All Employees (200 OK)
GET https://localhost:7069/api/employee
Accept: application/json

### Get Employee by ID (200 OK)
GET https://localhost:7069/api/employee/1
Accept: application/json

### Get Employee by Invalid ID (404 Not Found)
GET https://localhost:7069/api/employee/999
Accept: application/json

### Create New Employee (201 Created)
POST https://localhost:7069/api/employee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Williams",
  "email": "alice.williams@example.com",
  "department": "Marketing",
  "age": 29,
  "salary": 58000
}

### Create Employee with Invalid Data (400 Bad Request)
POST https://localhost:7069/api/employee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "A",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "department": "",
  "age": 15,
  "salary": -1000
}

### Update Employee (200 OK)
PUT https://localhost:7069/api/employee/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe Updated",
  "email": "john.doe.updated@example.com",
  "department": "IT Management",
  "age": 31,
  "salary": 65000
}

### Update Non-Existent Employee (404 Not Found)
PUT https://localhost:7069/api/employee/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "department": "Test",
  "age": 25,
  "salary": 50000
}

### Delete Employee (200 OK)
DELETE https://localhost:7069/api/employee/3

### Delete Non-Existent Employee (404 Not Found)
DELETE https://localhost:7069/api/employee/999
